[Leishmaniasis (visceral) in Argentina has previously been reported from Misiones and Corrientes provinces, and cutaneous leishmaniasis, along the northern border towards Brazil, and not in the province of Entre Rios. Entre Rios is bordering Corrientes to the north, and this seems to be one of the 1st reports of _Leishmania_ in dogs from Entre Rios, indicating that _Leishmania_ is spreading south in Argentina. ProMED will be happy to post further information - Mod.EP

